<br>
Maybe YOU never faught or suffered the effects of a battle torn country for the right or even ability to plant a crop. But somewhere here in America that fight was faught and there is reason to remember. <br>
<br>
The same battles that are happening abroad have happened here as well. Although they may be part of the distant past, they are still part of our history and rememberence isn't something you only do for your own trials for but for those whose trials are the foundation from which your lifestyle is based.<br>
<br>
Maybe the battles and wars we Americans are fighting today are not merited in the same way, but wars and battles have been faught and do merit a celebration. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=37659"><img  src="http://www.magelo.com/img/header.gif" border="0"></a></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uabbyssdd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abbyss DD</A> at: 6/4/02 11:01:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#353535><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Syna original</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(6/5/02 11:49:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclebloodcirclegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2038.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The more i think about it</span><hr size=1> Kinda off the subject of death and all that altogether i have been recently looking at the objective value of warfare in general.  At times in the past it intrigued me and at others it annoyed me.  But nowadays i am trying to understand the nature of human warfare within an evolutionary context, it is nothing new it has always been but why?  Looking at in from a modern perspective kinda distorts the model it was birthed in which is why i look at it from the coalitionary aspect adn the mate acquisition point of view.  In the old school a homeboy and his friends might have numbered about 150 friends or the size of a larger EQ guild.  Back in them days the earth consisted of about 200k political entities and there was constant warfare on a daily basis for most but for the dominant it was a little more relaxed liek each week.  Anyhow with the consolidation of 200k headmen int what we have today as about 200 headmen there was a lot of bloodhshed but in all there was less blood than there would have been had the 200k bossmen had achieved modern military technology.  If one looks at the middle east as an example or much of africa there you have a bunch of little units with good arms and alot of death (although not as much as full scale high tech).  When i look it in a historical context even the worst of it begins to make a little sense as leading to more peace through less variation of goals.   <br>
<br>
In the grander scheme of things i wonder if armed warfare has actually taken more lives than it has spared.  althogh the potential for destruction has indeed increased to about 4,000 per single wapon since hiroshima a remarkable few of them have actually been employed directly against populations (although about 1,000 of them have had latent functions like thyroid cancer through &quot;testing worldwide).  The net effect in multiplication of humans would seem to be positive.  In other words even though we have had some terrible encounters they have always failed to kill off even a single percentage point of the population at the time.  This is a claim something like a plague cannot make because they have traditionally wiped out significantly more.  <br>
<br>
In all i don't condone the behavior i am actually beginning to see a macroscopic value to the act of warfare.  One thing i can say for the ukraine is after around 20 million deaths last century between the nazi's on the russian front and the forced starvations led by the stalinist communists the survivors have left behind a fine stock of nice looking offspring <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclebloodcirclegeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=2038.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclebloodcirclegeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=2038.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclebloodcirclegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2038.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclebloodcirclegeneral.threadControl?topicID=2038.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclebloodcirclegeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2038.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclebloodcirclegeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2038.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub5.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1